description._content: Gottlieb, William P., 1917-, photographer. [Portrait of Helen Carr, Sammy Herman, Joe Bianco, and Donn Trenner, Nola's, New York, N.Y., ca. Feb. 1947] 1 negative : b&w ; 3 1/4 x 4 1/4 in. Caption from Down Beat: The Donn trio and Helen. Helen Carr, vocals; Sammy Herman, guitar; Joe Bianco, bass, and Donn Trenner, piano. Donn was with Ted Fio Rito ork. Herman was with TD for two years. Notes: Gottlieb Collection Assignment No. 261 Purchase William P. Gottlieb Forms part of: William P. Gottlieb Collection (Library of Congress). In: "Nola Studios is meeting place for NYC musicians," Down Beat, v. 14, no. 5 (Feb. 26, 1947), p. 15. Subjects: Carr, Helen Herman, Sammy Bianco, Joe Trenner, Donn Jazz musicians--1940-1950. Women jazz musicians--1940-1950. Nola's Format: Portrait photographs--1940-1950. Group portraits--1940-1950. Film negatives--1940-1950.
